<div class="container-fluid caitlin-custom-margin">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-6">
      <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-heading" style="background-color: #555">
          <h3 class="panel-title" style="font-size: x-large; color: white">Vision</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body" style="font-size: larger">
          <p>Build a knowledge graph that is open, accessible and community
            sourced. Under the stewardship of stakeholders from a diversity of organizations, Artsdata.ca is
            uniquely focused on the Canadian arts sector. The objectives are to:
            <ul class="custom-bullet">
              <li>Create an essential digital resource that reflects the values of the arts</li>
              <li>Build a substantial web of linked open data of arts-related information</li>
              <li>Provide high-quality data that is comprehensive and up to date</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div><!-- panel-body -->
      </div><!-- panel -->
    </div><!-- col -->

    <div class="col-sm-6">
      <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-heading" style="background-color: #555">
          <h3 class="panel-title" style="font-size: x-large; color: white">Benefits</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body" style="font-size: larger">
          <p>The Artsdata.ca knowledge graph enables the arts sector to:
            <ul class="custom-bullet">
              <li>Gain knowledge, agency and control of descriptive metadata about events, persons, organizations and venues</li>
              <li>Streamline the circulation of arts events to listings sites, recommenders and other search engines
                by programmatically sharing event metadata</li>
              <li>Optimize the use of the latest web technologies to generate new opportunities</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div><!-- panel-body -->
      </div><!-- panel -->
    </div><!-- col -->
  </div> <!-- row -->
