        <div class="panel-heading" style="background-color: #555">
          <h3 class="panel-title" style="font-size: x-large; color: white">Looking for a SPARQL endpoint?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body" style="font-size: larger">
          <p>Artsdata.ca works with SPARQL, a query language for linked open data and semantic graph databases. SPARQL
            users can query the knowledge graph using the provided YASGUI user interface or a remote SPARQL client.
            <br>
            <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="/sparql">Access SPARQL</a>
          </p>
          <br>
          <p>
            Sample SPARQL queries:
            <br>
            <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.event}">Events</a>
            <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.events_by_website}">Events by website</a>
            <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.artist}">Artists</a>
            <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.organization}">Organizations</a>
            <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.place}">Places</a>
            <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.provenance}">Provenance</a>
             <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.triple_count}">Triple Count</a>
             <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.catalog}">Meta Catalogs</a>
             <a class="btn btn-warning btn-lg" href="${get('config').sparqls.shacl_report}">SHACL Reports</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
